title: Brumm leads Kings to first win
text:
Brumm leads Kings to first win By: Uncredited Report Error 
David Brumm scored twice on Tuesday as the Dauphin Kings won their first game of the Manitoba Junior Hockey League season, 6-3 over the Waywayseecappo Wolverines. 
In other games, the Virden Oil Capitals rallied to beat the Swan Valley Stampeders 5-4 and the Winkler Flyers beat the Winnipeg Blues 3-2. 
In Waywayseecappo, Graeme Hore of Wawanesa had a goal and an assist for the Kings (1-2), as did Sam Schultz and Steven Sislo. Ty Enns of Cartwright scored for the Wolverines (0-2). 
Capitals 5 Stampeders 4 
In Virden, Cole Oliver of Melita scored the winner as the Oil Capitals (1-2) rallied with three goals in the third. Tanner Lewis of Virden had a goal and an assist for the Oil Caps, while Michael Fortin of Souris had a goal for the Stampeders (2-1). 
Flyers 3 Blues 2 
In Winkler, Zak Hicks of Boissevain opened the scoring for the Flyers (2-1) and Cam Whyte of Virden, and Jeff Michiels of Holland scored for the Flyers. With the loss, the Blues fell to 2-1.
